  "prompt": "On moon men feel lighter weight than earth?",
  "response": "Yes, people feel lighter on the Moon than on Earth. This is due to the difference in gravitational pull between the two celestial bodies. The Moon's gravity is only about 1/6th that of Earth's gravity. Therefore, if you weigh 180 pounds on Earth, you would weigh only about 30 pounds on the Moon. This reduced gravity makes you feel lighter and able to jump higher and carry heavier objects more easily compared to on Earth.",
